<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-29T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/3412a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-29T15:00:00-05:00">November 29, 1918—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Repeat to Quito, LaPaz, and Montevideo.</p>
                        <p>For your own information and in order to place you in a position to
                            answer any inquiries which may be made of you by the Government of the
                            country to which you are accredited, in regard to its presence at the
                            Peace Conference but not for formal communication to Foreign Office, the
                            Department sends you the following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The question of the representation at the peace conference of
                                    those countries which have broken relations with the Imperial
                                    German Government <pb facs="0295" n="225" xml:id="pg_225"/> but
                                    have not declared war, has not as yet been discussed by the
                                    associated governments. Until such discussion is held and some
                                    decision arrived at, it will be impossible to make any statement
                                    in this connection.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>